Title: S06E08 - Breaking Barriers: Unleashing Accessible Software for All with Dennie Declercq
Description: Dennie Declercq, an accessibility advocate and MVP, sheds light on the importance of accessibility in software development. With engaging discussions and thought-provoking facts, the podcast explores how inclusive design can be applied to various forms of software, including web, mobile, and desktop applications. Declercq emphasizes the role of assistive technologies, the significance of alt tags, the impact of accessibility on SEO, the value of transcriptions, and the guidelines provided by the WCAG. By framing accessibility in terms of increased sales and visibility, developers can effectively communicate its importance to decision-makers. This podcast offers valuable insights and practical advice for creating more inclusive software.
